A man who was rushed to hospital with a metal chair leg embedded in his skull after a bar brawl has stunned doctors by making a remarkable recovery.

X-rays of the man's injury in Siberia, Russia, show the stool leg stuck more than four inches into his brain.

The man spent more than two weeks in intensive care after being attacked in a bar but he is now on the way to making a full recovery.

